x(4-x)
(a-b)(a+b)=a^2-b^2.
pq
a
b
p=a+b
q=a-b
p=x+1
q=5-x
 p+q=(a+b)+(a-b)=2a \implies a=\frac{p+q}2. 
 p-q=(a+b)-(a-b)=2b\implies b=\frac{p-q}2. 
 a=\frac{p+q}2=\frac{(x+1)+(5-x)}2=\frac62=3 
 b=\frac{p-q}2=\frac{(x+1)-(5-x)}2=\frac{x+1-5+x}2=\frac{2x-4}2=x-2. 
 (x+1)(5-x)=pq=a^2-b^2=3^2-(x-2)^2 
x(4-x)
x(4-x)=4x-x^2=\color{blue}{+4}\color{red}{-4}+4x-x^2=\color{blue}{+4}\color{red}{-}(\color{red}{4}\color{blue}{-}4x\color{blue}{+}x^2)=\color{blue}{2^2}\color{red}{-}(x-2)^2
